tion, suggesting a\nnonprimordial origin for dwarf spheroidal satellite galaxies, which we\nspeculate were formed via a top-down fragmentation process as the result of\nnonlinear dissipative collapse of larger density perturbation. This could\nexplain the planar orientation of satellite galaxies around Andromeda and the\nMilky Way.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Feb 2016 05:55:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 4 May 2016 23:39:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 16 Jun 2016 01:21:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-13"}
